message.content:
A warthog is a wild pig species found in Africa.
It has a distinctive appearance with a large head, large curved tusks, and warty protrusions on its face that give it its name.
The warthog's fur is sparse and bristly with brownish-grey coloring, and its skin has a tough texture.
It has a stocky and muscular build with short legs and a high-set tail that hangs down like a plume.
Warthogs are omnivorous and feed on roots, tubers, and small animals.
They are known for their speed and agility, often fleeing from predators by running at high speeds and changing directions suddenly.
Warthogs can be found in grasslands, savannas, and woodlands across sub-Saharan Africa.
